This paper deals with the problem of selecting a set of alternatives based on the preferences of agents, which is a central problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the complexity of computing and verifying Pareto optimal outcomes, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.LG). Finally, the paper considers strategic issues and presents a strategyproof algorithm, which is relevant to social and information networks (cs.SI).
